tral framework. Using\nthem, we illustrate how entanglement and classicality of an observed system\ndepend on the quantum frame perspective. Our operational language also inspires\na new interpretation of Dirac and reduced quantized theories within our model\nas perspective-neutral and perspectival quantum theories, respectively, and\nreveals the explicit link between them. In this light, we suggest a new take on\nthe relation between a `quantum general covariance' and the diffeomorphism\nsymmetry in quantum gravity.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 3 Sep 2018 11:25:31 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 25 Mar 2019 17:50:42 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Mon, 23 Dec 2019 16:31:32 GMT"},{"version":"v4","created":"Wed, 22 Jan 2020 12:54:52 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-01-29"}
