 and Lubotzky-Oppenheim. We suggest a more\nflexible notion of stability that may repair this deficiency of stability with\nrespect to\n$\\left(\\operatorname{U}\\left(n\\right),d_{n}^{\\operatorname{HS}}\\right)$ and\n$\\left(\\operatorname{Sym}\\left(n\\right),d_{n}^{\\operatorname{Hamming}}\\right)$.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 3 Sep 2018 15:49:20 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Fri, 22 Feb 2019 11:44:32 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-02-25"}
